{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82dbc9ce-ef6d-49c9-8439-2f5e04746453","content":"The issue is clear. In F#, **file compilation order matters** — files can only reference modules defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_5q5kMSX3T7lN0nG4fJzIBo","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-dcb7dc767aed4df8badc30ce3ec25213/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-dcb7dc767aed4df8badc30ce3ec25213/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"fc0e8926-f598-4ad0-9711-e792ace9dd59","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed earlier in the project file. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), and `Program.fs` depends on both. So `Domain.fs` must come first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the `<Compile>` items so that `Domain.fs` comes first, then `Services.fs`, then `Program.fs`.","outputTokens":472,"requestId":"5C01:1295A2:1DDDA76:21A2622:6A07C8BA"},"id":"27a1a739-cd47-4e1b-889e-7d49e983692a","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:30:42.131Z","parentId":"6922b81b-6c07-4650-80e7-4336c4d7347d"}
